# LLM Wiki (Karpathy pattern)

## Purpose

Turn substantive work into a **durable knowledgebase**—facts, constraints, decisions, and “do not repeat” mistakes—using Karpathy’s [LLM Wiki pattern](https://gist.github.com/karpathy/442a6bf555914893e9891c11519de94f).

This file is the **authoritative spec** for wiki layering, how agents maintain markdown, and **`@wiki-lint`**. Do not duplicate that contract under `docs/`. **Roles:** the user steers topics; agents write and cross-link pages, keep the catalog and log current, and evolve this rule with the human. Triggers and repo-wide routing: [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).

## Layers

**Flow:** raw drops → curated wiki → ops contract (this rule; human + agent).

| Layer | Location | Who edits |
|-------|----------|-----------|
| Raw sources (immutable) | [`wiki/raw/`](../../wiki/raw/) | Human drops files; agents read only |
| Wiki pages + catalog | [`wiki/`](../../wiki/) ([`wiki/index.md`](../../wiki/index.md), [`wiki/log.md`](../../wiki/log.md)) | Agents create/update pages, cross-links, index, and log |
| Ops contract (when/how to maintain the wiki) | This file (`.cursor/rules/llm-wiki.mdc`) | Human + agent co-evolve |

## Operations (at a glance)

- **Ingest** — Read sources or conversation; write/update wiki pages; refresh the index; append the log.
- **Query** — Read `wiki/index.md` first, then drill into linked pages; file durable answers back into the wiki.
- **Lint** — On request, when the wiki is large, or when the user invokes **`@wiki-lint`** — follow [**Lint**](#lint) below.

## When to update (no reminder needed)

Do **not** wait for “put this in the wiki.” After **substantive** work (research, debugging, design, ops), if **any** of this became true, integrate before you stop:

- Non-obvious fact, constraint, or command that will matter in a **later** session.
- A mistake, false assumption, or fix worth **not repeating**.
- A stable decision or rationale **not** captured in an ADR, plan file, or scoped pipeline artifact.
- A good synthesis, comparison, or answer the user might ask again — **file it**, not only chat.

Skip trivia, secrets, one-off typos, or anything already the single source of truth in `pipelines/` scoped output or upstream submodule docs (link instead).

## What to touch each time

1. **Create or edit** the relevant topic/entity pages under `wiki/` (relative links between pages).
2. Update [`wiki/index.md`](../../wiki/index.md): entry or one-line summary per page; keep categories honest.
3. Append one line to [`wiki/log.md`](../../wiki/log.md): `## [YYYY-MM-DD] ingest \| Short title` or `query \|`, `lint \|`, `update \|` as appropriate.

Optional **raw** inputs for later ingest live only under [`wiki/raw/`](../../wiki/raw/) (immutable for agents — summarize into wiki pages, do not edit sources).

## Query habit

When the user asks something that may already be compiled, **read `wiki/index.md` first**, then open linked pages. Prefer citing/updating the wiki over rediscovering from scratch.

## Lint

**Purpose:** Review `wiki/` for consistency and navigability. May propose or apply **markdown-only** fixes (cross-links, index rows, log append); do **not** modify files under [`wiki/raw/`](../../wiki/raw/).

Run a lint pass when the user asks to clean up the wiki, invokes **`@wiki-lint`**, or pages grow stale.

### When the user invokes `@wiki-lint`

Respond with:

1. **Scope:** All markdown under [`wiki/`](../../wiki/) except [`wiki/raw/`](../../wiki/raw/) (immutable sources).
2. **Findings:** Contradictions between pages; stale or superseded claims; orphan pages (no inbound link from [`wiki/index.md`](../../wiki/index.md) or another wiki page); broken relative links; index entries pointing to missing files; important topics mentioned without a page.
3. **Actions:** List concrete edits (paths + intent). Apply fixes when safe; otherwise leave as recommendations.
4. **Log:** If any wiki file changed, append an entry to [`wiki/log.md`](../../wiki/log.md): `## [YYYY-MM-DD] lint | Short summary`.
